<p>From 24th to 26th November 2014, Guam will lead the Pacific Region for the next international TAFISA CLC. Guam is a beautiful tropical isle in the western Pacific “Where America’s day begins.” Guam’s 212 square miles and 170,000 population make it the largest island in Micronesia. Guam’s average temperature is 75° – 88° F or 23° – 29° C. While its main languages are English and Chamorro (indigenous language), Guam has a very diverse cross-cultural populace. </p><p>Guam has beautiful white sand beaches, several golf courses, and significant historical sites from the Spanish era and from WWII. Guam has been a U.S. Territory since 1898. Guam’s currency is the U.S. dollar. Guam enters its own delegation in the Olympic Games.</p><p>The Guam CLC will be in the Westin Resort GUAM (105 Gun Beach in Tumon, Tel (671) 647-1020). The Westin Resort is an upscale 4-star hotel and spa, sits directly upon a beautiful stretch of beach ideal for water sports. The hotel has 7 onsite dining options, plus pools with pool bar. The Westin has excellent conference/training facilities and is within easy walking distance of excellent shopping, diverse restaurants, and entertainment.</p><p>More information <a href="http://www.tafisa.net/images/stories/pdfs/clc2014/GuamCLCBrochure2014.pdf">here</a>.</p>